trust_ratings table:
rater(account_id) ratee(account_id) trust(float) type(string)


The UI will allow users to edit their rating of other users. (simple number input on user's page). type = user_to_user.


Platform's ratings may be represented by some admin user. These will be computed based on how many social logins the user has authenticated with. type = social_logins.


The default condition type w will sum up the ratings of all types coming from 3 entities: user itself, campaign maintainer, and platform admin.


















ALTER TABLE public.accounts ALTER COLUMN id ADD GENERATED ALWAYS AS IDENTITY (
    SEQUENCE NAME public.users_id_seq
    START WITH 1
    INCREMENT BY 1
    NO MINVALUE
    NO MAXVALUE
    CACHE 1
);


ALTER TABLE public.causes ALTER COLUMN id ADD GENERATED ALWAYS AS IDENTITY (
    SEQUENCE NAME public.causes_id_seq
    START WITH 1
    INCREMENT BY 1
    NO MINVALUE
    NO MAXVALUE
    CACHE 1
);


ALTER TABLE public.campaigns ALTER COLUMN id ADD GENERATED BY DEFAULT AS IDENTITY (
    SEQUENCE NAME public.campaigns_id_seq
    START WITH 1
    INCREMENT BY 1
    NO MINVALUE
    NO MAXVALUE
    CACHE 1
);

ALTER TABLE public.participations ALTER COLUMN id ADD GENERATED ALWAYS AS IDENTITY (
    SEQUENCE NAME public.participation_id_seq
    START WITH 1
    INCREMENT BY 1
    NO MINVALUE
    NO MAXVALUE
    CACHE 1
);





